.SH NAME
.PP
apm-pkg \[en] Atom.io package manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]apm-pkg\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]command\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Manage Atom.io apm with \f[C]$ATOM_PACKAGES_FILE\f[R] manifest file, by
default located at \f[C]\[ti]/.atom/packages.txt\f[R].
.PP
This wrapper extends \f[B]apm\f[R] with \f[C]install\f[R] and
\f[C]dump\f[R] commands that allow installing packages with a manifest
file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \f[C]-h\f[R], \f[C]--help\f[R]
Print help.
.TP
.B \f[C]-v\f[R], \f[C]--version\f[R]
Print version number.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B \f[C]dump\f[R] [\f[I]filename\f[R]]
Dump list of installed packages to the manifest file.
.TP
.B \f[C]install\f[R] [\f[I]filename\f[R]]
Install packages listed in the manifest file.
.TP
.B \f[C]list\f[R]
List installed packages.
.TP
.B \f[C]lock\f[R]
List installed packages and versions.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B \f[C]ATOM_PACKAGES_FILE\f[R]
Path to the packages manifest file.
.SH FILES
.PP
Depends on external programs \f[C]apm\f[R], \f[C]awk\f[R],
\f[C]bash\f[R], \f[C]cat\f[R] and \f[C]sort\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Dump packages:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ apm-pkg dump
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Install packages:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
$ apm-pkg install
\f[R]
.fi
